&quot; The older man said with a smile.<br><br>   &quot;That was yesterday... Father.. you know she's as fickle as an elf sometimes.. Mother is sound asleep, these trips are very taxing on her, seeing as she is still with child.&quot; A young man stated as he emerged from the wagon to sit next to his elder and sister.<br><br>  &quot;Yes, Arathyn, I know.. but there is no other way, coin has been very scarce for us, but hopefully we can sell our wares in Freeport, I've heard tale that these arms are in very high demand there. Here.. your sister has fallen asleep... It will be dark soon, and very cold.. take her back and bundle her up.&quot;<br><br>     The dark-haired young man nodded, and took the frail little child into his arms, he smiled sadly to her, seeing how thin she has become, none of them have been eating well, bread and water mostly. He layed her down and wrapped her in blankets. As usual when he had time alone he started to handle the wares, his hands found their way around the hilt of a claymore, he lifted it high into the air, straining to keep it aloft. Swinging it slowly he drifted off into a daydream....<br><br>    Riding upon a magnificent steed, the knight charged into battle, what foe would he face this day? A horrible dragon? Armies of orcs? The hideously evil Iksarr? Or leigons of the Undea-<br><br>    Arathyn is jarred out of his daydreams by the sudden stop of the wagon.<br><br>    &quot;Father?, Is everything all right? Are we stopping for the night?&quot; He called out to the front of the wagon, but there was no answer. Gripping the blade tightly he emerges from the covered wagon, but is greeted only by the night sky and a cold wind. Jumping onto the sand, what his eyes met, horrified him, the tunic his father was wearing, torn and bloodied. He gasped and stepped back, a taloned hand gripped his shoulder and he felt his legs no longer responding, the smell of death and decay assaulted his nostrils, twirling around he lifted the sword high and cleaved with all his might, the blade struck home on the foul ghoul, one of a large pack that chose the small wagon as their food for the eve. Then there was a crack... and shatter as the blade exploded in shards of metal, the ghoul, almost seeming to laugh, tossed Arathyn to the side and clamored with his companions into the wagon.<br><br>                        *********************************<br><br>     &quot;Sir Darkmoore? They... they didn't make it...&quot;<br><br>     &quot;I see. That is most unfortunate...&quot; Caine Darkmoore said as he finished off the last of the ghouls. &quot;That boy... he had a lot of spirit... if he weren't so Scrawny.. he would have made a fine Steel Warrior.. &quot;<br><br>    &quot;Sir! He's......... He's still alive!! Badly wounded... and his hair... it's gone white!&quot;<br><br>    &quot;Come.. quickly now.. lets go.. we'll take him to the Temple of Marr.. they'll help...&quot;<br><br><br><br><br>-Arathyn Shadowsbane<br>Knight in Shining Armor (Though still in training)  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umelmell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>melmell</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.theorderofthedragon.com/docs/fanart/cross.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>A_Idiot_666</span><br>  Posts: 193<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/5/02 8:15:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://a0.cpimg.com/image/8A/36/8501130-86a6-00800074-.jpg height=145 width=128></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> sounds coo